Police in Kisumu have arrested a suspect for allegedly threatening to kill the Kisumu National Polytechnic principal Catherine Kelonye. The suspect, Philimon Bulwa, 42, was also accused of creating disturbances at the polytechnic where is a trainer. Kisumu Central sub-county police commander Anthony Maina confirmed the arrest of the suspect. Maina said the suspect was arrested by officers from Kondele Police Station after Kelonye reported the case. Bulwa, an ex-prison officer, was expected to be arraigned at Winam Law court on Monday for the offences. This follows the recommendation from the Office of the Director of Public Prosecution (ODPP), Nyanza region. “The case was investigated and the file forwarded to ODPP for perusal and advice,” Maina aid.